messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path:
- /printshops/{id}/reviews

All methods acceptable:
- false

Per-method acceptance (based on the code):
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping (only @RestController), so the method-level values are the full paths.
- getPrintShopReviews is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/reviews", method = RequestMethod.GET) — therefore GET is accepted for /printshops/{id}/reviews.
- addPrintShopReview is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}/reviews", method = RequestMethod.POST) — therefore POST is accepted for the same path.
- The PUT and DELETE handlers exist but are mapped to "/printshops/{printShopId}/reviews/{reviewId}" (they require a {reviewId} path segment), so they do not apply to "/printshops/{id}/reviews".
- No handler in the code declares HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PATCH, or a wildcard (no-method) mapping for this exact path, so those methods are not considered acceptable here. (Per the instructions, only mappings explicitly present in the code were used — framework implicit behavior such as automatic HEAD handling is not assumed.)
